                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I would not go as far as to say &quot;Forget about all the 3rd party libraries&quot;. JsonUtility has limitations. It does not return a JSON object on which you can perform actions. For instance, I get a json file and want to check whether a &quot;success&quot; key is available. Can&apos;t do. The JsonUtility requires the consumer knows the exact content of the json file. Also, no Dictionary converter. So it does some good things but the usage of 3rd party is still required.&lt;/span&gt;

